{
  "name": "add-a-message-queue-to-the-20260414-1343",
  "idea": "Add a message queue to the Timeline Agent chat in reigh-app/src/tools/video-editor/components/AgentChat. Currently the input is blocked while a message is sending. Goal: let the user type and submit subsequent messages while the agent is still processing the current one. Queued messages should display stacked above the chat input, each with a delete button and reorder (up/down) controls. When the active send completes (and agent finishes its turn), the next queued message auto-sends. Keep scope minimal \u2014 local client-side queue only, no server/DB changes. Existing files: AgentChat.tsx (main component with handleSend, sendingRef, optimisticMessage, draft state), AgentChatMessage.tsx. Attachments (clips) should be captured at the time of queueing so the user can change their selection for subsequent queued messages.",
